# Agent Smart Account Rule

- Use the MetaMask Smart Accounts Toolkit (old MetaMask Delegation Toolkit) for all smart-account and delegation behavior.
- Do not use Privy built-in smart accounts, Privy delegation helpers, or any Privy-specific smart-account abstraction in this project.
- Use Privy only for auth plus wallet access.
- The smart account used for auth, delegation, session packaging, and downstream authorization must be the MetaMask-toolkit smart account associated with the registered gym agent.
- Wallet signing priority is strict:
  1. Use the connected MetaMask EOA wallet when available.
  2. Only if MetaMask is not connected, use the Privy embedded social wallet EOA.
- Never fall back to a Privy smart account or Privy delegation path.
- Treat agent registration and delegation/session-package bootstrap as separate flows.
- If the registered agent exists but delegation/session state is missing, do not redirect to registration. Fail explicitly or start the delegation bootstrap flow.
- When validating auth, target the registered MetaMask-toolkit smart account and its associated owner EOA, not a Privy smart account abstraction.
